Small HOWTO for releasing versions.

0) Change VERSION file.
1) Maybe adjust UPGRADE file.
2) Tag the whole tree with: (after everything being commited!)
     svn cp $SVNREP/okuson/trunk $SVNREP/okuson/tags/tag-1r2
   This works completely in the repository!
     The environment variable SVNREP must be set to 
     svn://thuban.math.rwth-aachen.de/home2/thuban/svnuser
3) Export the whole tree (somewhere else) with:
     svn co $SVNREP/okuson/tags/tag-1r2 okuson
     (this generates a directory "okuson" in the current directory).
4) Go to this new directory:
   cd okuson
5) Make archive:
   ./makeArchive
   (the exported tree is modified substantially!)
   You find ../okuson-1.*.pdf and ../okuson-1.*.tar.gz .
6) Copy those to  a checked out okuson directory.
   Use 'cd website; cptoweb' to update the web site.
7) Inform interested user.


------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Backup:
   Old version for cvs for step 2, not used any longer:

   cvs tag -F tag-1r1       (or tag-1r1f2)
           ^ This forces tags even to files which are already tagged with
             this tag!
   Old version for cvs for step 3, not used any longer:

   cvs -d :pserver:neunhoef@antares.math.rwth-aachen.de:2401/home/antares/neunhoef/cvsrepository export -r tag-1r1 okuson
